Muri Kanama 2011, Fondasiyo ya Sitade ya Cricket mu Rwanda yashinzwe mu gikorwa cy’urukundo, ikora nka sosiyete idashingiye ku nyungu, hagamijwe ko yubaka  ikanacunga ikibuga cy’imikino mpuzamahanga cya mbere cyeguriwe [[Rwanda|u Rwanda]] . kubaka iki kibuga byarangiye muri Werurwe 2017.  Iherereye kuri hegitari 4.5 ku nkombe ya [[Kigali]], umurwa mukuru [[Rwanda|w'u Rwanda.]] <ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/feb/15/rwanda-cricket-stadium-massacre-site Cricket stadium to rise in shadow of Rwandan massacre]</ref>   Kuri ubu stade yakira amarushanwa ya Kwibuka Women T20 ngarukamwaka, 

Iyi nkunga iyobowe n'itsinda ry'abakunzi ba Cricket baturutse mu [[Ubwongereza|Bwongereza]] no mu [[Rwanda]] ku bufatanye na Fondasiyo ya Marylebone Cricket Club.

Mu mwaka wa 2012, Brian Lara <ref>[http://www.cricketintheparks.org.uk/#!rwandan-cricket-foundation/c93s UNIVERSITY CRICKET at OXFORD]</ref> yemeye kuba umwe mu ba Patron b'ubutaka. Iyi Sitade kandi ishyigikiwe n’uwahoze ari Minisitiri w’intebe w’Ubwongereza, David Cameron , Andrew Mitchell, Jonathan Agnew, Heather Knight, Peter Gummer, Baron Chadlington <ref>[http://mccfoundation.co.uk/398/rwanda-2/ MCC]</ref> <ref>[http://s.telegraph.co.uk/graphics/projects/Fields-Of-Dreams/index.html Field of dreams]</ref>

Muri 2018, ikibanza cyatoranijwe kugirango kizakire imikino mumatsinda ya 2018–19 ICC World Twenty20 Africa Qualifier Itsinda ryiburasirazuba.   

Iyi stade kandi yakiriye amarushanwa ya T20 y'abagore ya Kwibuka ya 2019,  amarushanwa ya Cricket y'abagore, mu rwego rwo kwibuka abishwe na [[jenoside yo mu [[Itsembabwoko ry’u Rwanda ry’1994|Rwanda]] mu 1994. 

